      "job_description": "Note: This job is on-site in Chicago. We are not looking for software / backend / React / Angular / Vue developers for this position.\n\nWho We Are:\n\nDHD is a small, collaborative Chicago agency (46 years young!) specializing in marketing websites, emails, and interactive tools for diverse clients. We value curiosity, independence, and craftsmanship. We're looking for a talented and versatile Web Designer & Front-End Developer to join our team, someone who can both design compelling user experiences and build them with clean, production-ready code. Our ideal candidate is passionate about good design, has a keen eye for detail, and thrives in a self-directed role, often being the sole technical expert on projects.\n\nCore Responsibilities:\n\nDesign & Build:\n‚Ä¢ Create and extend design direction: Take basic art direction and independently build out UI elements, brochure sites and landing pages from raw assets to finely tuned deployments.\n‚Ä¢ CMS Integration & Theming: Build and integrate front-end UI with various CMS systems, primarily Craft CMS and WordPress (with occasional HubSpot, Squarespace, Framer, Drupal, etc.). This includes CMS content population, theming, and templating (Twig, ACF, PHP).\n‚Ä¢ Code Quality & Testing: Ensure clean code, browser compatibility, and accessibility across all projects.\n\nEmail Marketing & Development:\n‚Ä¢ Responsive Email Development: Design, code, and test responsive emails in Mailchimp, Campaign Monitor, HubSpot, and client CRMs (e.g., Salesforce Marketing Cloud), ensuring cross-client compatibility.\n‚Ä¢ Campaign Management: Manage the email deployment calendar for a range of clients.\n‚Ä¢ Performance Analysis: Analyze and communicate e-marketing campaign metrics with clients and internal stakeholders.\n\nTech Exploration & Team Support:\n‚Ä¢ Workflow Optimization: Experiment with AI tools and other technologies to streamline design and development workflows (e.g., content generation, image optimization).\n‚Ä¢ Adaptability: Adapt to various client tech stacks and project methodologies.\n‚Ä¢ Light IT Troubleshooting: Assist colleagues with basic IT troubleshooting (email, connectivity, basic SaaS tools).\n\nSkills We Need:\n\nMust-Haves:\n‚Ä¢ Visual Design Proficiency: Strong visual design chops with expert proficiency in Figma/Adobe XD and Adobe Creative Suite (you'll design and implement).\n‚Ä¢ Front-End Development Mastery: Firm understanding and hands-on experience with HTML5, CSS3, Sass, Tailwind/Bootstrap, and JavaScript/jQuery.\n‚Ä¢ CMS Expertise: Extensive experience with Craft CMS and WordPress theming/templating, including Twig and PHP.\n‚Ä¢ Email Development Expertise: Proven experience with Mailchimp, Campaign Monitor, and hand-coding responsive email templates across multiple email clients.\n‚Ä¢ Version Control: Proficiency with Git for code versioning.\n‚Ä¢ Independent Work Style: Ability to thrive in a self-directed role and manage projects from start to finish with minimal oversight.\n‚Ä¢ Analytical Skills: Ability to configure and run reports for Google Analytics/Tag Manager and interpret campaign data.\n‚Ä¢ Work Portfolio: A strong portfolio showcasing at least 3+ marketing sites/emails you built, demonstrating your design and coding capabilities.\n\nNice-to-Haves:\n‚Ä¢ Working knowledge of build tools such as Vite, Webpack.\n‚Ä¢ Experience with Docker and DDEV.\n‚Ä¢ Analytics ‚Äî work with SEM specialist to configure and run reports for Google Analytics/Tag Manager and interpret campaign data\n‚Ä¢ Basic IT troubleshooting skills (O365, Wi-Fi, permissions).\n‚Ä¢ Experience with HubSpot or Framer.\n‚Ä¢ Curiosity about AI/automation for marketing workflows.\n‚Ä¢ Previous agency experience.\n\nWhat We Don‚Äôt Need:\n‚Ä¢ Backend engineers (we generally use CMS backends, not custom APIs).\n‚Ä¢ Full-stack developers focused on complex applications (no React/Angular/Vue apps here).\n‚Ä¢ DevOps/cloud architects (we host on managed servers).\n\nWork Style:\n‚Ä¢ Small Team = Big Impact: You'll own projects start-to-finish and have a direct impact on client success.\n‚Ä¢ Flexible Processes: We prioritize great communication and results over rigid agile/waterfall methodologies or daily stand-ups.\n‚Ä¢ Creative Collaboration: You'll partner closely with designers, copy writers and the client team to bring innovative marketing ideas to life.\n\nBenefits:\n‚Ä¢ Medical health benefits\n‚Ä¢ 401K plan with company match\n‚Ä¢ Energetic, collaborative work environment\n‚Ä¢ Close to public transportation\n\nApply If You:\n‚Ä¢ Have a portfolio showing 3+ marketing sites/emails you built (required).\n‚Ä¢ Can describe your process for building a CMS template from a Figma file.\n‚Ä¢ Enjoy the variety of troubleshooting a printer between coding sessions.\n‚Ä¢ Possess a positive attitude and a willingness to continuously learn and stay up-to-date on best practices in web design and development.\n\nJob Type: Full-time\n\nPay: $70,000.00 - $85,000.00 per year\n\nBenefits:\n‚Ä¢ 401(k)\n‚Ä¢ 401(k) matching\n‚Ä¢ Health insurance\n‚Ä¢ Paid time off\n\nSchedule:\n‚Ä¢ Monday to Friday\n\nApplication Question(s):\n‚Ä¢ Can you provide a link to your web design portfolio?\n\nExperience:\n‚Ä¢ Craft CMS: 1 year (Required)\n\nLocation:\n‚Ä¢ Chicago, IL 60601 (Required)\n\nAbility to Commute:\n‚Ä¢ Chicago, IL 60601 (Required)\n\nWork Location: In person",
